<DESCRIPT>  FRUIT; RECIPE  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  Sweet red beauties offer; one of summer's treats  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Food  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  CHERRY CHEER  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Recipes of the Week  </MEMO>
<TEXT>  for pies, salads, chutney; or just to dip and savor; NORTHWEST CHERRY;
CHUTNEY;  1 quart fresh sweet cherries, pitted;  1 quart pitted peaches, cut
in eighths;  2 1/2 cups packed brown sugar;  2 cups cider vinegar;  1 medium
lemon, seeded and chopped;  1/2 cup each raisins and chopped onion;  3
tablespoons minced fresh ginger root;  1 1/2  teaspoons salt;  1 clove garlic,
minced;  1/2 teaspoon crushed hot red pepper;  Combine all ingredients; mix
well. Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer about 2 hours or until mixture
thickens; stir frequently. Ladle into clean hot canning jars to within 1/4
inch of tops. Seal according to jar manufacturer's directions. Place jars on
rack in canner. Process 15 minutes in boiling water bath with boiling water
two inches above jar tops. Remove jars from canner. Place on thick cloth or
wire racks. Cool away from drafts. After 12 hours test lids for proper seal;
remove rings from sealed jars. Makes about 5 half-pints.;    Note: Serve with
poultry or pork.; One tablespoon: 39 calories; .1 gm. fat, 43 mg. sodium and 0
mg. cholesterol.;  SUPER CHERRY PIE; 4 cups pitted fresh sweet cherries; 3
cups pared, cored and sliced Granny Smith apples;  1/4 cup sugar; 2
tablespoons flour; 1 teaspoon vanilla;  1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon;  1/4
teaspoon ground ginger; 2 tablespoons butter or margarine;  Pastry for
two-crust 9-inch pie;   Combine cherries and apples in large bowl. Add sugar,
flour, vanilla and spices; mix well. Place mixture in pastry-lined 9-inch pie
plate. Dot with butter. Roll and cut remaining pastry into 3/4-inch strips.
Weave over fruit, lattice-fashion; seal and flute edges. Bake at 425 degrees
for 25 minutes; reduce heat to 400 degrees. Bake 20 minutes longer or until
fruit is tender and filling begins to bubble. If necessary, cover edges of pie
with foil partway through cooking time to prevent overbrowning.;    Note:
Quick method of baking: Microwave pie at high 10 to 12 minutes, or until
filling begins to bubble. Bake at 425 degrees for 10 to 15 minutes or until
pastry browns.; One serving: 384 calories; 21 gm. fat, 304 mg. sodium and 8
mg. cholesterol.;  TROPICAL CHERRY SALAD;  2 cups fresh sweet cherries, pitted
if desired;  1 large mango, peeled, pitted and sliced;  1 cup fresh or 1 8
1/2-ounce can pineapple chunks;  4 to 6 large lettuce leaves;  1/4 cup
coarsely chopped macadamia nuts or pecan halves;   Lime Dressing (recipe
follows);   Arrange cherries, mango and pineapple on lettuce-lined platter;
sprinkle nuts over fruit. Drizzle with Lime Dressing or pass dressing with
salad. Makes 2 or 3 servings.; One serving: 371 calories; 15 gm. fat, 7 mg.
sodium and 0 mg. cholesterol.;  Lime Dressing: Combine 2 tablespoons each
honey, lime juice and pineapple juice or syrup and 1/4 teaspoon grated lime
peel. Slowly blend in 1/4 cup vegetable oil. Makes about 1/2 cup.; One
tablespoon: 79 calories; 7 gm. fat, trace sodium and 0 mg. cholesterol.; 
CHERRY DIP; 1  3-ounce package cream cheese, softened; 2 tablespoons
mayonnaise; 1 teaspoon lemon juice; 2 tablespoons powdered sugar; 1 tablespoon
milk;  1/2 teaspoon almond extract;  Fresh sweet cherries;   Blend all
ingredients except cherries. Serve with fresh or frozen cherries. Makes 3/4
cup.; One tablespoon: 47 calories; 4 gm. fat, 35 mg. sodium and 10 mg.
cholesterol.;  CITRUS CREAM DIP; 1 cup dairy sour cream; 1 tablespoon lemon
juice; 1 tablespoon powdered sugar; 1 teaspoon grated orange peel;  Dash of
salt;   Fresh sweet cherries;   Blend all ingredients except cherries. Serve
with fresh or frozen cherries. Makes 1 cup.; One tablespoon: 33 calories; 3
gm. fat, 16 mg. sodium and 8 mg. cholesterol.;  FRESH NORTHWEST CHERRY SALSA; 
1 cup pitted fresh sweet cherries;  2 tablespoons chopped fresh basil;  1
tablespoon finely chopped green peppers;  1 teaspoon lemon juice;  1/4
teaspoon each Worcestershire sauce and grated lemon peel;  1/8 teaspoon salt; 
 Dash bottled hot pepper sauce;   Chop cherries manually or in food processor.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Makes about
1/4 cup. Recipe may be doubled.;    Note: Serve with chicken, pork or
whitefish. Best served fresh. Flavors dilute with storage.; One serving: 10
calories; .1 gm. fat, 24 mg. sodium and 0 mg. cholesterol.;  GREEN BEANS WITH
CHERRIES;  1/2 pound green beans; 1 cup cherries, pitted; 1  to 2 tablespoons
butter, cut in pea-sized pieces; 2 tablespoons chopped parsley;  1/2 clove
garlic, minced; 1 tablespoon fresh tarragon, chopped;   Salt and pepper to
taste;   Trim the ends of the green beans. Then cut them French-style,
lengthwise on a steep diagonal so that each piece is approximately 1 inch long
and 1/4 inch wide. Blanch in boiling salted water until tender, about 4 or 5
minutes. Drain in a colander and refresh under cold water. Put beans in a dry
skillet and heat until the surface moisture evaporates. Add remaining
ingredients, tossing to coat well. Correct seasonings and serve at once. Makes
3 to 4 servings.;    -- From "From a Breton Garden" by Josephine Araldo and
Robert Reynolds (Aris Books, $22.95)  </TEXT>
